author: Jacksonville State Athletics
title: Jax State remains No. 1 in football polls
text:
The Jacksonville State football team solidified its hold on the top spot in the STATS FCS Top 25 and moved up one spot to second in the Coaches Poll on Monday.
Fresh off a 42-13 win at Tennessee Tech, the Gamecocks (5-1, 3-0 Ohio Valley Conference) took advantage of a loss by North Dakota State, who was No. 2 in both polls last week. JSU received several votes that were going to the Bison in both polls before they fell at home to South Dakota on Saturday.
JSU received 108 first-place votes in the STATS Poll, 19 more than last week, and received 3,897 total votes. Coastal Carolina, who was off on Saturday, moved up one spot from No. 3, receiving 27 first-place and 3,743 total votes. Illinois State, James Madison and Chattanooga each moved up one spot to round out the Top five, respectively. NDSU fell to eighth. It marks the sixth-straight week that JSU has been atop the STATS Poll.
In the Coaches Poll, the Gamecocks climbed one spot to second but trail first place Coastal Carolina by just 15 total votes. CCU received 15 first-place votes to JSU's five and got 610 total points to the Gamecocks' 595. James Madison is third in the Coaches Poll, while Illinois State and Chattanooga are fourth and fifth, respectively.
The Gamecocks will play on the road again Saturday, when they travel to Clarksville, Tenn., for a 4 p.m. meeting with Austin Peay. The game will be broadcast on the OVC Digital Network and on the Gamecock Sports Network. JSU returns home for the first time in four weeks on Oct. 31 for Homecoming against Eastern Kentucky, who is ranked 14th in the Coaches Poll and 13th in the STATS Poll.
